  "body": "\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\n obc deletion fails for brownfield cases\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nobc should delete properly\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\nkubectl delete -f <path for obc -retain.yaml>\r\n\r\nRCA :\r\nUser unlink is performed on bucket before deleting the user fails.\r\nThe \"user unlink\" will only for the existing owner of the bucket, here user the created by the operator have access to the bucket via bucket policy. So dropping the policy for that user is only enough\r\n\r\n",
